H.B. 295
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
Mar 5, 2025
SESSION 2025
HOUSE PRINCIPAL CLERK
H D
HOUSE BILL DRH30130-BG-1A
Short Title: Req. DOT to Install Prop. Corner Markers. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative Gillespie.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO REQUIRE THE NORTH CAROLINA DEPARTMENT OF TRANSPORTATION
3 TO INSTALL PROPERTY CORNER MARKERS ALONG CERTAIN PROPERTY
4 ACQUISITIONS AFTER PROJECT COMPLETION.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6 SECTION 1. G.S. 136-19.4A reads as rewritten:
7 "§ 136-19.4A. Required surveying information in certain acquisition plans.plans;
8 installation of property-related corner markers.
9 (a) Surveying Information Required. – The Department of Transportation shall include
10 in any plan prepared for the purpose of acquiring right-of-way, a permanent easement, or both,
11 that depicts property lines, right-of-way lines, or permanent easements, a set of drawings that
12 clearly identify design alignments, baseline control points, found property-related corner
13 markers, and new right-of-way and permanent easement corner markers. Plans subject to the
14 requirements of this section shall document the localized coordinates for each major control point
15 along the design alignments. The coordinates and associated localization metadata shall be based
16 upon, and tied to, the North Carolina State Plane Coordinate system and shall be clearly identified
17 within the plans. All property corner markers found found, identified, and surveyed shall be
18 clearly identified within the plans in accordance with general surveying standards and
19 procedures. Each property corner marker shall be accurately tied to the design alignment or the
20 North Carolina State Plane Coordinate system, by either a system of bearings and distances or
21 by station and offset. For the purposes of this section, the phrase "new right-of-way and
22 permanent easement corner markers" must include all property boundary intersections along
23 right-of-way or permanent easements acquired by the Department.
24 (b) Installation of New Right-of-Way and Permanent Easement Corner Markers. – The
25 Department of Transportation shall survey and install new right-of-way and permanent easement
26 corner markers utilizing metal stakes, or materials of comparable permanence, along
27 right-of-way or permanent easements acquired by the Department, as described in subsection (a)
28 of this section, in accordance with general surveying standards and procedures after the
29 completion of a project for which right-of-way or permanent easements were acquired."
30 SECTION 2. This act is effective when it becomes law and applies to Department
31 of Transportation projects initiated on or after that date that require right-of-way or permanent
32 easement acquisition.
*DRH30130-BG-1A*

